<p>Sound localization is important for everyday hearing. With <a href="http://www.ece.mcmaster.ca/~ibruce/">Dr. Ian Bruce</a> at McMaster University, I used computational models of the auditory brainstem and midbrain to investigate how sound localization cues are processed in impaired and aided hearing.</p>

